WEBVTT

00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:08.809 align:middle line:90%
[ Music ]

00:00:20.087 --> 00:00:22.823 align:middle line:84%
>> Lisa Garr: Hi, I'm Lisa Garr
host of Gaiam Inspirations.

00:00:22.823 --> 00:00:26.327 align:middle line:84%
Would you like to know
what God looks like?

00:00:26.327 --> 00:00:29.396 align:middle line:84%
How about heaven, would you like
to know what heaven looks like?

00:00:29.396 --> 00:00:30.998 align:middle line:84%
Well, these are not
the questions

00:00:30.998 --> 00:00:34.635 align:middle line:84%
that Harvard train neurosurgeon
Dr. Eben Alexander was asking

00:00:34.635 --> 00:00:36.303 align:middle line:90%
himself when a rare form

00:00:36.303 --> 00:00:39.707 align:middle line:84%
of meningitis attacked his
brain causing him to go

00:00:39.707 --> 00:00:42.376 align:middle line:90%
into a coma for seven days.

00:00:42.376 --> 00:00:44.211 align:middle line:84%
And what he found
there, he describes

00:00:44.211 --> 00:00:47.181 align:middle line:90%
in his book as Proof of Heaven.

00:00:47.181 --> 00:00:49.884 align:middle line:84%
Welcome to the show,
thank for being here.

00:00:49.884 --> 00:00:50.718 align:middle line:84%
>> Eben Alexander:
Well, thank you Lisa,

00:00:50.718 --> 00:00:52.052 align:middle line:90%
it's so good to be here.

00:00:52.052 --> 00:00:54.455 align:middle line:84%
>> Lisa Garr: It gives me
chills to even say that opening,

00:00:54.455 --> 00:00:57.525 align:middle line:84%
what you have been through,
and what you're here to share

00:00:57.525 --> 00:00:59.560 align:middle line:90%
with us is extraordinary.

00:00:59.560 --> 00:01:03.030 align:middle line:84%
So, let's start up talking a
little bit about your experience

00:01:03.030 --> 00:01:05.666 align:middle line:84%
as a neurosurgeon,
as a man of science

00:01:05.666 --> 00:01:09.303 align:middle line:84%
and all the research
that you did.

00:01:09.303 --> 00:01:13.174 align:middle line:84%
How does that come into play
with your experience now,

00:01:13.174 --> 00:01:15.042 align:middle line:90%
being a man of science?

00:01:15.042 --> 00:01:16.310 align:middle line:84%
>> Eben Alexander: Well, I
think the important thing

00:01:16.310 --> 00:01:20.247 align:middle line:84%
to understand, I had grown
up in a scientific family.

00:01:20.247 --> 00:01:22.550 align:middle line:84%
My father very much
is a scientist.

00:01:22.550 --> 00:01:25.019 align:middle line:84%
He was neurosurgeon, head
of a training program.

00:01:25.019 --> 00:01:26.854 align:middle line:84%
So, he trained other
neurosurgeons.

00:01:26.854 --> 00:01:28.923 align:middle line:90%
He was also very spiritual.

00:01:28.923 --> 00:01:33.360 align:middle line:84%
So, I had both those things
in my upbringing and went

00:01:33.360 --> 00:01:37.765 align:middle line:84%
to a Methodist Church and I'm--
much my life wanted to believe

00:01:37.765 --> 00:01:41.168 align:middle line:84%
in God, and heaven,
and power of prayer,

00:01:41.168 --> 00:01:45.605 align:middle line:84%
but through a long career
in neurosurgery, you know,

00:01:45.605 --> 00:01:49.476 align:middle line:84%
15 years at Harvard Medical
School, dealing with thousands

00:01:49.476 --> 00:01:51.845 align:middle line:84%
of patients, many
of them had been

00:01:51.845 --> 00:01:54.147 align:middle line:90%
in coma for various reasons.

00:01:54.147 --> 00:01:56.516 align:middle line:90%
I found it harder and harder

00:01:56.516 --> 00:01:59.954 align:middle line:84%
to explain how consciousness
could survive death

00:01:59.954 --> 00:02:01.989 align:middle line:90%
of the body and brain.

00:02:01.989 --> 00:02:07.394 align:middle line:84%
And so, in fact when I went
into coma in 2008, I was driven

00:02:07.394 --> 00:02:12.666 align:middle line:84%
into coma very rapidly within
a few hours by a severe case

00:02:12.666 --> 00:02:16.003 align:middle line:84%
of bacterial meningitis that by
all right should have killed me.

00:02:16.003 --> 00:02:17.404 align:middle line:84%
>> LG: And what is
the percentage

00:02:17.404 --> 00:02:19.607 align:middle line:90%
of people that it does kill?

00:02:19.607 --> 00:02:25.012 align:middle line:84%
>> EA: Well, bacterial
meningitis is a 100 percent

00:02:25.012 --> 00:02:27.114 align:middle line:90%
fail, if not treated.

00:02:27.114 --> 00:02:30.551 align:middle line:84%
Even when treated rapidly
with the right antibiotics,

00:02:30.551 --> 00:02:35.623 align:middle line:84%
most series it's still 30
to 40-- 50 percent fail.

00:02:35.623 --> 00:02:39.593 align:middle line:84%
And in fact in my particular
case, given that I went

00:02:39.593 --> 00:02:42.863 align:middle line:84%
into coma within about
3 and a half or 4 hours

00:02:42.863 --> 00:02:43.831 align:middle line:90%
of unsettled symptoms.

00:02:43.831 --> 00:02:44.665 align:middle line:90%
>> LG: Wow.

00:02:44.665 --> 00:02:46.433 align:middle line:90%
>> EA: That in itself when I got

00:02:46.433 --> 00:02:47.835 align:middle line:84%
to the emergency
room I was found

00:02:47.835 --> 00:02:51.437 align:middle line:84%
to have bacterial meningitis,
going into coma that quickly

00:02:51.437 --> 00:02:54.842 align:middle line:84%
with bacterial meningitis
takes you to about a 10 percent

00:02:54.842 --> 00:02:57.778 align:middle line:84%
or less survival
for that illness.

00:02:57.778 --> 00:03:00.381 align:middle line:84%
By the end of the week,
when I was not responding

00:03:00.381 --> 00:03:03.183 align:middle line:84%
to antibiotics, that was down
to about a 2 or 3 percent chance

00:03:03.183 --> 00:03:05.719 align:middle line:84%
of survival with no
chance of recovery.

00:03:05.719 --> 00:03:08.222 align:middle line:84%
>> LG: What happens to the
brain when you have that type

00:03:08.222 --> 00:03:10.157 align:middle line:90%
of a bacterial infection?

00:03:10.157 --> 00:03:12.960 align:middle line:84%
>> EA: Well, it actually
is the most perfect model

00:03:12.960 --> 00:03:16.263 align:middle line:84%
of human death, because
that kind

00:03:16.263 --> 00:03:19.166 align:middle line:84%
of bacterial infection
attacks the neocortex,

00:03:19.166 --> 00:03:23.070 align:middle line:84%
it attacks the entire
outer surface of the brain.

00:03:23.070 --> 00:03:26.206 align:middle line:84%
And that's the part that
absolutely crucial for all

00:03:26.206 --> 00:03:28.342 align:middle line:90%
of our human consciousness.

00:03:28.342 --> 00:03:32.079 align:middle line:84%
All the details of our
conscious awareness

00:03:32.079 --> 00:03:35.883 align:middle line:84%
since before we were born,
everything we see, hear are kind

00:03:35.883 --> 00:03:40.086 align:middle line:84%
of a logical, rational
thinking language, understanding

00:03:40.086 --> 00:03:44.258 align:middle line:84%
of our surroundings and
of our body position

00:03:44.258 --> 00:03:46.994 align:middle line:84%
and space every bit
of that requires

00:03:46.994 --> 00:03:50.331 align:middle line:84%
that complex calculator
of the neocortex.

00:03:50.331 --> 00:03:55.636 align:middle line:84%
And that's why, severe bacterial
meningitis was such a gift,

00:03:55.636 --> 00:03:59.640 align:middle line:84%
because it basically
attacked all of that

00:03:59.640 --> 00:04:02.309 align:middle line:84%
and should have taken me
down to a level according

00:04:02.309 --> 00:04:05.512 align:middle line:84%
to modern neuroscience where
I would have only the most

00:04:05.512 --> 00:04:08.115 align:middle line:84%
rudimentary form
of consciousness

00:04:08.115 --> 00:04:09.516 align:middle line:90%
which I describe in my book.

00:04:09.516 --> 00:04:12.019 align:middle line:84%
I think that that
earthworm's eye view was

00:04:12.019 --> 00:04:17.358 align:middle line:84%
that rudimentary course, kind
of unresponsive consciousness

00:04:17.358 --> 00:04:19.326 align:middle line:90%
that one could have when most

00:04:19.326 --> 00:04:22.896 align:middle line:84%
of their neocortex has been
killed off by bacteria.

00:04:22.896 --> 00:04:25.199 align:middle line:84%
>> LG: The most simplest
form of consciousness,

00:04:25.199 --> 00:04:27.001 align:middle line:84%
is that what you mean
very uncomplicated?

00:04:27.001 --> 00:04:30.671 align:middle line:84%
>> EA: Well, a very kind of
simplistic rudimentary form

00:04:30.671 --> 00:04:34.641 align:middle line:84%
of awareness that would be
completely non interactive,

00:04:34.641 --> 00:04:37.678 align:middle line:84%
non aware, I mean in
that original state,

00:04:37.678 --> 00:04:40.147 align:middle line:90%
in that earthworm eye view--

00:04:40.147 --> 00:04:41.882 align:middle line:84%
>> LG: Earthworm eye view,
what do you mean by that?

00:04:41.882 --> 00:04:44.418 align:middle line:84%
>> EA: That was-- that's
how I describe in my book

00:04:44.418 --> 00:04:46.320 align:middle line:90%
that first realm that I was in--

00:04:46.320 --> 00:04:47.588 align:middle line:90%
>> LG: OK.

00:04:47.588 --> 00:04:49.790 align:middle line:84%
>> EA: Which is basically
a very course underground

00:04:49.790 --> 00:04:54.128 align:middle line:84%
where like being in dirty
jello and totally unresponsive.

00:04:54.128 --> 00:04:58.499 align:middle line:84%
People had often asked me
was that hell or purgatory?

00:04:58.499 --> 00:05:01.135 align:middle line:84%
I would think hell would be at
least a little bit interactive

00:05:01.135 --> 00:05:04.438 align:middle line:84%
and this was not at all
interactive even though

00:05:04.438 --> 00:05:10.277 align:middle line:84%
that meningitis that very simple
course consciousness involve no

00:05:10.277 --> 00:05:14.982 align:middle line:84%
recollection whatsoever of my
life before, nothing at all

00:05:14.982 --> 00:05:19.386 align:middle line:84%
of language, no knowledge of
earth, humans, absolutely zero

00:05:19.386 --> 00:05:21.989 align:middle line:84%
about Eben Alexander, certainly
not any of my religions

00:05:21.989 --> 00:05:23.690 align:middle line:90%
or any other kind of background.

00:05:23.690 --> 00:05:28.529 align:middle line:84%
All that was completely wiped
out which enabled my NDE

00:05:28.529 --> 00:05:31.498 align:middle line:84%
to have some unusual
features that are a typical,

00:05:31.498 --> 00:05:34.835 align:middle line:84%
and yet I look at them,
it's making it the exception

00:05:34.835 --> 00:05:38.105 align:middle line:84%
that proves the rule,
that validates millions

00:05:38.105 --> 00:05:40.274 align:middle line:90%
of other similar stories.

00:05:40.274 --> 00:05:41.275 align:middle line:90%
>> LG: Yes.

00:05:41.275 --> 00:05:43.110 align:middle line:84%
Did you ever have
a form and opinion

00:05:43.110 --> 00:05:45.112 align:middle line:90%
of near death experiences before

00:05:45.112 --> 00:05:47.281 align:middle line:84%
when you were practicing
as a neurosurgeon?

00:05:47.281 --> 00:05:50.317 align:middle line:84%
Did you ever have
an opinion of those?

00:05:50.317 --> 00:05:51.685 align:middle line:90%
>> EA: I was-- before my coma,

00:05:51.685 --> 00:05:56.790 align:middle line:84%
I was very much a card toadying
conventional neuroscientist.

00:05:56.790 --> 00:05:59.960 align:middle line:84%
I believed completely in
what they called reductive

00:05:59.960 --> 00:06:02.529 align:middle line:84%
materialist view of
the world that is

00:06:02.529 --> 00:06:04.965 align:middle line:84%
if you can explain everything
in terms of electrons,

00:06:04.965 --> 00:06:07.935 align:middle line:84%
corks [phonetic], protons,
neutrons, the physics,

00:06:07.935 --> 00:06:11.638 align:middle line:84%
chemistry, biology that you
can then explain everything

00:06:11.638 --> 00:06:13.407 align:middle line:90%
about all of the existence.

00:06:13.407 --> 00:06:16.043 align:middle line:84%
The only problem with that
conventional science is I came

00:06:16.043 --> 00:06:18.912 align:middle line:90%
to see it after my coma is

00:06:18.912 --> 00:06:25.018 align:middle line:84%
that that conventional science
has not the most primitive

00:06:25.018 --> 00:06:28.655 align:middle line:84%
explanation whatsoever for how
the physical brain might give

00:06:28.655 --> 00:06:29.957 align:middle line:90%
rise to consciousness.

00:06:29.957 --> 00:06:32.226 align:middle line:84%
And that's a tremendous
red flag.

00:06:32.226 --> 00:06:33.293 align:middle line:90%
>> LG: Interesting.

00:06:33.293 --> 00:06:34.862 align:middle line:84%
As you had said once
in your book

00:06:34.862 --> 00:06:38.832 align:middle line:84%
that the body can actually
function without or is it

00:06:38.832 --> 00:06:41.602 align:middle line:90%
without the use of the heart--

00:06:41.602 --> 00:06:44.004 align:middle line:84%
the brain, is that
what you've said?

00:06:44.004 --> 00:06:45.372 align:middle line:90%
>> EA: Well, that the--

00:06:45.372 --> 00:06:47.541 align:middle line:84%
>> LG: The death of the body
and the brain are not the end

00:06:47.541 --> 00:06:48.275 align:middle line:90%
of consciousness you said.

00:06:48.275 --> 00:06:49.676 align:middle line:90%
>> EA: Right.

00:06:49.676 --> 00:06:53.046 align:middle line:84%
Exactly, in fact with my coma
journey showed me very clearly.

00:06:53.046 --> 00:06:55.815 align:middle line:84%
And this was that gift of
severe bacterial meningitis

00:06:55.815 --> 00:06:57.084 align:middle line:90%
that should've killed me

00:06:57.084 --> 00:07:02.422 align:middle line:84%
or at least absolutely
limited my conscious experience

00:07:02.422 --> 00:07:04.324 align:middle line:84%
to the most rudimentary
as opposed

00:07:04.324 --> 00:07:08.061 align:middle line:84%
to the most incredible ultra
real vibrant journey life

00:07:08.061 --> 00:07:12.299 align:middle line:84%
changing that I could ever
imagine which is what happened.

00:07:12.299 --> 00:07:15.135 align:middle line:84%
And there was no place in
my brain for that to unfold.

00:07:15.135 --> 00:07:19.773 align:middle line:84%
Before my coma, being that
conventional neuroscientist,

00:07:19.773 --> 00:07:22.643 align:middle line:84%
I thought with the brain
creates consciousness.

00:07:22.643 --> 00:07:25.345 align:middle line:84%
So, when the brain and
body die, that's the end

00:07:25.345 --> 00:07:26.980 align:middle line:90%
and that is absolutely false.

00:07:26.980 --> 00:07:28.382 align:middle line:90%
I've come to realize.

00:07:28.382 --> 00:07:31.517 align:middle line:84%
I never paid any attention to
the near death literature before

00:07:31.517 --> 00:07:36.256 align:middle line:84%
because my physical is mind set,
it's set its all birth to death

00:07:36.256 --> 00:07:38.025 align:middle line:84%
and the brain creates
consciousness--

00:07:38.025 --> 00:07:38.859 align:middle line:90%
>> LG: Right.

00:07:38.859 --> 00:07:39.993 align:middle line:90%
>> EA: I had absolutely no way

00:07:39.993 --> 00:07:44.064 align:middle line:84%
to understand how those
phenomenon could occur.

00:07:44.064 --> 00:07:49.236 align:middle line:84%
So, I was unwilling to look at
the data and come to understand

00:07:49.236 --> 00:07:52.239 align:middle line:84%
that there are tens of
thousands of reports out there

00:07:52.239 --> 00:07:54.508 align:middle line:84%
and the similarity is
far away the differences.

00:07:54.508 --> 00:07:55.809 align:middle line:90%
>> LG: Absolutely.

00:07:55.809 --> 00:07:57.611 align:middle line:84%
So, I have a question about
your book in the prologue.

00:07:57.611 --> 00:07:59.413 align:middle line:84%
Why did you make the
choice to tell us

00:07:59.413 --> 00:08:03.750 align:middle line:84%
about your incredible
sky diving experiences?

00:08:03.750 --> 00:08:05.986 align:middle line:90%
You were an avid sky diver.

00:08:05.986 --> 00:08:09.856 align:middle line:84%
You loved flying
since you're a child.

00:08:09.856 --> 00:08:11.391 align:middle line:90%
What is the correlation there?

00:08:11.391 --> 00:08:14.728 align:middle line:84%
>> EA: Well, I think
to me and looking back

00:08:14.728 --> 00:08:18.532 align:middle line:84%
on it especially it became
clear that I was always trying

00:08:18.532 --> 00:08:20.601 align:middle line:90%
to get up above this world.

00:08:20.601 --> 00:08:25.105 align:middle line:84%
It's like I felt more at
home being up and above.

00:08:25.105 --> 00:08:28.642 align:middle line:84%
And, you know, as
I tell my book I--

00:08:28.642 --> 00:08:34.080 align:middle line:84%
when I was 14 years old I
soloed in sailplanes and to me--

00:08:34.080 --> 00:08:35.415 align:middle line:90%
>> LG: 14.

00:08:35.415 --> 00:08:38.986 align:middle line:84%
>> EA: -- at 14 and I was
just always wanting to be up,

00:08:38.986 --> 00:08:42.623 align:middle line:84%
whether if it's climbing trees
when I was a young kid or,

00:08:42.623 --> 00:08:47.361 align:middle line:84%
you know, I was pole vaulting
in high school, the sailplanes

00:08:47.361 --> 00:08:50.364 align:middle line:84%
at age 14, and the sky
diving all through college.

00:08:50.364 --> 00:08:55.102 align:middle line:84%
It was always about trying
to get into a higher realm

00:08:55.102 --> 00:08:58.805 align:middle line:84%
and I think in a sense that
serves as kind of a metaphor

00:08:58.805 --> 00:09:00.374 align:middle line:90%
for what I ended up doing--

00:09:00.374 --> 00:09:01.475 align:middle line:90%
>> LG: Absolutely.

00:09:01.475 --> 00:09:03.143 align:middle line:84%
>> EA: -- in my big
journey, deep in coma.

00:09:03.143 --> 00:09:06.980 align:middle line:84%
>> LG: So, you're into the
wormhole experience of--

00:09:06.980 --> 00:09:09.449 align:middle line:84%
I just called it a wormhole
you said-- you called it a--

00:09:09.449 --> 00:09:10.250 align:middle line:90%
>> EA: Earthworm's eye view.

00:09:10.250 --> 00:09:11.518 align:middle line:90%
>> LG: Earthworm's eye view.

00:09:11.518 --> 00:09:16.490 align:middle line:84%
So, then you enter to this
incredible blissful state.

00:09:16.490 --> 00:09:18.925 align:middle line:90%
Tell us about that.

00:09:18.925 --> 00:09:22.362 align:middle line:84%
>> EA: Well, the--
that initial realm,

00:09:22.362 --> 00:09:24.131 align:middle line:84%
as I said I had no
language and a word,

00:09:24.131 --> 00:09:25.699 align:middle line:90%
no memory of my life before,

00:09:25.699 --> 00:09:27.901 align:middle line:84%
that was that earthworm
eye view.

00:09:27.901 --> 00:09:32.372 align:middle line:84%
And that amnesia from my life
before was present throughout

00:09:32.372 --> 00:09:33.773 align:middle line:90%
this journey.

00:09:33.773 --> 00:09:37.611 align:middle line:84%
It's very important because it
led this on atypical features

00:09:37.611 --> 00:09:41.114 align:middle line:84%
because many souls who go
into near death experience

00:09:41.114 --> 00:09:46.219 align:middle line:84%
and comeback to talk about it
go in and have some knowing

00:09:46.219 --> 00:09:50.724 align:middle line:84%
of an identity and of their
relationship with other souls.

00:09:50.724 --> 00:09:52.926 align:middle line:84%
And it's important
that in my journey

00:09:52.926 --> 00:09:55.929 align:middle line:84%
and of course originally
I explained all this

00:09:55.929 --> 00:09:59.166 align:middle line:84%
because of the severe
bacterial meningitis wiping

00:09:59.166 --> 00:10:00.734 align:middle line:90%
out my neocortex.

00:10:00.734 --> 00:10:02.703 align:middle line:84%
I now know their
far deeper reasons

00:10:02.703 --> 00:10:04.971 align:middle line:84%
for why it all unfolded
the way it did.

00:10:04.971 --> 00:10:09.976 align:middle line:84%
But that was the explanation
it was necessary at that time.

00:10:09.976 --> 00:10:12.713 align:middle line:84%
And then from that
realm I was rescued

00:10:12.713 --> 00:10:16.883 align:middle line:84%
by the slowly spinning
pure white light

00:10:16.883 --> 00:10:18.118 align:middle line:90%
that came towards me.

00:10:18.118 --> 00:10:21.388 align:middle line:84%
I remembered it looked
liked it had a surface kind

00:10:21.388 --> 00:10:25.225 align:middle line:84%
of a ground glass but it
was a very pure clear light

00:10:25.225 --> 00:10:28.995 align:middle line:84%
where these fine white and gold
filaments coming off of it.

00:10:28.995 --> 00:10:31.365 align:middle line:84%
>> LG: Kind of ever
decent opalescent?

00:10:31.365 --> 00:10:33.734 align:middle line:84%
>> EA: It was very
much an opalescent--

00:10:33.734 --> 00:10:34.601 align:middle line:90%
>> LG: Yes.

00:10:34.601 --> 00:10:36.336 align:middle line:90%
>> EA: -- orb of light.

00:10:36.336 --> 00:10:42.242 align:middle line:84%
Very clear, very pure and it had
the most perfect musical melody.

00:10:42.242 --> 00:10:46.313 align:middle line:84%
And it came towards me
very slowly spinning.

00:10:46.313 --> 00:10:48.849 align:middle line:84%
And as it did I was just
captivated by this light

00:10:48.849 --> 00:10:52.452 align:middle line:84%
and then it opened up
like a rip in the fabric

00:10:52.452 --> 00:10:56.556 align:middle line:84%
of that gross earthworm
eye view realm and lit

00:10:56.556 --> 00:10:59.826 align:middle line:90%
up into this brilliant valley

00:10:59.826 --> 00:11:05.599 align:middle line:84%
into what I call the Gateway
Valley, the gateway realm.

00:11:05.599 --> 00:11:13.240 align:middle line:84%
And the vivid ultra real nature
of that valley is something

00:11:13.240 --> 00:11:16.376 align:middle line:84%
that is so far beyond words,
I was moving up through it

00:11:16.376 --> 00:11:20.514 align:middle line:84%
because I was a spec of
awareness, on a butterfly away.

00:11:20.514 --> 00:11:23.650 align:middle line:84%
Now, of course, you know,
the skeptics hear butterfly

00:11:23.650 --> 00:11:26.219 align:middle line:84%
and they hear the rest of this
beautiful earth-like valley

00:11:26.219 --> 00:11:28.188 align:middle line:90%
and they get a little mislead.

00:11:28.188 --> 00:11:30.323 align:middle line:84%
They start thinking, well,
this is just trappings

00:11:30.323 --> 00:11:32.359 align:middle line:90%
of your brain before in kind

00:11:32.359 --> 00:11:35.195 align:middle line:84%
of earth-like stop
that got layered on.

00:11:35.195 --> 00:11:37.130 align:middle line:84%
And I think there is some
of that for some people,

00:11:37.130 --> 00:11:39.433 align:middle line:84%
for me that's a lot less
convincing because I had

00:11:39.433 --> 00:11:43.470 align:middle line:84%
such a complete destruction
of my neocortex that allowed

00:11:43.470 --> 00:11:44.871 align:middle line:90%
for a lot of this to unfold.

00:11:44.871 --> 00:11:47.707 align:middle line:84%
>> LG: And you saw that through
the-- this-- the brain scans?

00:11:47.707 --> 00:11:49.009 align:middle line:90%
>> EA: Oh yeah.

00:11:49.009 --> 00:11:50.677 align:middle line:84%
Through the brain scans and
neurologic exams, I mean,

00:11:50.677 --> 00:11:54.481 align:middle line:84%
it was very clear that the
meningitis had severely attacked

00:11:54.481 --> 00:11:56.283 align:middle line:90%
my neocortex.

00:11:56.283 --> 00:11:58.952 align:middle line:84%
And that's what was
causing the coma.

00:11:58.952 --> 00:12:01.922 align:middle line:84%
I mean, I looked-- I also
knew all the drugs I was on,

00:12:01.922 --> 00:12:04.991 align:middle line:84%
I knew the drug doses all
through the week correlated

00:12:04.991 --> 00:12:08.528 align:middle line:84%
with the neurologic exams,
correlated with the scans.

00:12:08.528 --> 00:12:11.598 align:middle line:84%
So, it was clear to me, I
went into coma, you know,

00:12:11.598 --> 00:12:14.034 align:middle line:90%
in my home-- in my bed at home.

00:12:14.034 --> 00:12:20.040 align:middle line:84%
I had seizures and then was
comatose intermittently seizing

00:12:20.040 --> 00:12:24.778 align:middle line:84%
and then maybe out of deep coma
but certainly not conscious

00:12:24.778 --> 00:12:28.582 align:middle line:84%
at all for the-- at first hour
to into the emergency room.

00:12:28.582 --> 00:12:31.451 align:middle line:84%
And then my exams from
that point on showed

00:12:31.451 --> 00:12:33.753 align:middle line:84%
that my neurologic
function declined.

00:12:33.753 --> 00:12:36.957 align:middle line:84%
They did have me on sedatives
during some of that time.

00:12:36.957 --> 00:12:39.226 align:middle line:84%
>> LG: But none of those
had psychotropic effects?

00:12:39.226 --> 00:12:41.061 align:middle line:84%
>> EA: Well, they could
have if I'd had much

00:12:41.061 --> 00:12:43.296 align:middle line:90%
of a neocortex left to function.

00:12:43.296 --> 00:12:48.134 align:middle line:84%
But in fact, by that time,
my neocortex was not working.

00:12:48.134 --> 00:12:52.138 align:middle line:84%
And that was documented in the
neurologic exams that showed

00:12:52.138 --> 00:12:55.475 align:middle line:84%
that happening and then
on scans on several days,

00:12:55.475 --> 00:13:00.947 align:middle line:84%
CT-scans showing that I had
swelling through both sides,

00:13:00.947 --> 00:13:02.883 align:middle line:90%
hemispheres all eight lobes

00:13:02.883 --> 00:13:06.653 align:middle line:84%
and was even losing what's
called the gray-white junction

00:13:06.653 --> 00:13:08.521 align:middle line:84%
at the depth-- the
deepest layers

00:13:08.521 --> 00:13:12.325 align:middle line:84%
of a neocortex was
starting to melt away due

00:13:12.325 --> 00:13:13.627 align:middle line:90%
to the effect of the meningitis.

00:13:13.627 --> 00:13:16.529 align:middle line:84%
>> LG: It is amazing you're
even sitting here talking

00:13:16.529 --> 00:13:19.266 align:middle line:90%
like you are without any damage.

00:13:19.266 --> 00:13:22.402 align:middle line:84%
>> EA: I think that's one of
the things that was so shocking.

00:13:22.402 --> 00:13:25.338 align:middle line:84%
And of course I didn't realize
at first how shocking that was.

00:13:25.338 --> 00:13:26.473 align:middle line:90%
>> LG: Because you [inaudible]--

00:13:26.473 --> 00:13:27.807 align:middle line:84%
>> EA: Because I had no
idea how sick I'd been.

00:13:27.807 --> 00:13:32.145 align:middle line:84%
And when I fist came back,
from coma, it's also important

00:13:32.145 --> 00:13:36.148 align:middle line:84%
to point out that my brain
had been badly damaged.

00:13:36.148 --> 00:13:36.816 align:middle line:90%
>> LG: Yes.

00:13:36.816 --> 00:13:37.350 align:middle line:90%
>> EA: My language--

00:13:37.350 --> 00:13:38.585 align:middle line:90%
>> LG: Yeah.

00:13:38.585 --> 00:13:39.953 align:middle line:84%
>> EA: -- was just beginning
to come back when I woke

00:13:39.953 --> 00:13:44.291 align:middle line:84%
up on the 7th day and when they
took out the breathing tube.

00:13:44.291 --> 00:13:46.326 align:middle line:90%
And so, language was coming back

00:13:46.326 --> 00:13:48.662 align:middle line:84%
but I remembered
nothing of my life.

00:13:48.662 --> 00:13:54.067 align:middle line:84%
And two of my sisters spent
nights in my ICU room with me.

00:13:54.067 --> 00:13:57.103 align:middle line:84%
They would kind of relive
some of our family memories

00:13:57.103 --> 00:13:59.406 align:middle line:84%
of vacations, when we're
kids and things like that.

00:13:59.406 --> 00:14:02.876 align:middle line:84%
They tell me stories that
initially to me were fascinating

00:14:02.876 --> 00:14:04.377 align:middle line:90%
but I wasn't part of them.

00:14:04.377 --> 00:14:06.513 align:middle line:84%
But then slowly that
started triggering

00:14:06.513 --> 00:14:07.714 align:middle line:90%
and bringing things back.

00:14:07.714 --> 00:14:10.684 align:middle line:84%
So, over a few weeks, a
lot of my kind of family

00:14:10.684 --> 00:14:12.052 align:middle line:84%
and childhood memories
came back.

00:14:12.052 --> 00:14:13.320 align:middle line:84%
>> LG: Oh, that was
nice of them.

00:14:13.320 --> 00:14:16.489 align:middle line:84%
I went though the same
experience where I--

00:14:16.489 --> 00:14:19.893 align:middle line:84%
I had a near death experience
and went to that beautiful place

00:14:19.893 --> 00:14:22.729 align:middle line:84%
that I called Oneness but
out of it I lost my memory

00:14:22.729 --> 00:14:24.297 align:middle line:90%
for good three months.

00:14:24.297 --> 00:14:28.301 align:middle line:84%
>> EA: Well, a lot of my
memories of life before

00:14:28.301 --> 00:14:34.741 align:middle line:84%
like knowledge of consciousness
of brain mind of physics,

00:14:34.741 --> 00:14:38.778 align:middle line:84%
chemistry, all of that took up
to six weeks or so to come back.

00:14:38.778 --> 00:14:41.648 align:middle line:84%
So, that was very
important because I went--

00:14:41.648 --> 00:14:44.451 align:middle line:84%
when I first came back
within a few days,

00:14:44.451 --> 00:14:46.453 align:middle line:84%
I knew every bit
of where I'd been.

00:14:46.453 --> 00:14:47.988 align:middle line:90%
That story--

00:14:47.988 --> 00:14:48.922 align:middle line:90%
>> LG: That was--

00:14:48.922 --> 00:14:50.123 align:middle line:84%
>> EA: -- was rich
as could be and

00:14:50.123 --> 00:14:53.226 align:middle line:84%
yet I remembered nothing
of life before coma.

00:14:53.226 --> 00:14:55.829 align:middle line:90%
And so, while, and of course

00:14:55.829 --> 00:14:58.231 align:middle line:84%
when I would tell my doctors
some of what I remembered,

00:14:58.231 --> 00:14:59.733 align:middle line:84%
they would pat me
on the back and say,

00:14:59.733 --> 00:15:02.035 align:middle line:90%
"Oh, you were very sick.

00:15:02.035 --> 00:15:05.939 align:middle line:84%
Your brain was so damaged
by this meningitis.

00:15:05.939 --> 00:15:09.209 align:middle line:84%
There is no way you could have
had any experience like that.

00:15:09.209 --> 00:15:10.877 align:middle line:90%
So, you can forget about it."

00:15:10.877 --> 00:15:13.046 align:middle line:84%
You know, the dying brain
does all kinds of tricks.

00:15:13.046 --> 00:15:14.247 align:middle line:90%
>> LG: OK.

00:15:14.247 --> 00:15:15.648 align:middle line:84%
>> EA: I didn't know any
better so I believed them.

00:15:15.648 --> 00:15:17.851 align:middle line:84%
You know, most people believe
their doctors so I'd say, "OK,

00:15:17.851 --> 00:15:19.486 align:middle line:84%
a dying brain could
do any trick."

00:15:19.486 --> 00:15:23.690 align:middle line:84%
But I gleaned enough from
that that to realize there had

00:15:23.690 --> 00:15:26.526 align:middle line:84%
to be some kind of lesson
in there about consciousness

00:15:26.526 --> 00:15:29.062 align:middle line:84%
because I knew what
I remembered.

00:15:29.062 --> 00:15:31.097 align:middle line:84%
And I remembered a
very vivid odyssey,

00:15:31.097 --> 00:15:33.633 align:middle line:84%
if you'd ask me how long
I've been in that coma.

00:15:33.633 --> 00:15:35.835 align:middle line:84%
I would have said at
least months maybe years.

00:15:35.835 --> 00:15:39.606 align:middle line:84%
It means a long very
extensive odyssey.

00:15:39.606 --> 00:15:43.109 align:middle line:84%
And so, I knew there had to be
some kind of lesson in there

00:15:43.109 --> 00:15:46.112 align:middle line:84%
about consciousness because my
doctors were telling me nothing

00:15:46.112 --> 00:15:48.114 align:middle line:84%
could have happened,
your brain was too sick.

00:15:48.114 --> 00:15:50.617 align:middle line:84%
>> LG: Can you go back to this
spec on the butterfly wing

00:15:50.617 --> 00:15:55.121 align:middle line:84%
that you were and that feeling
not even a feeling it was an

00:15:55.121 --> 00:15:57.523 align:middle line:84%
experience that you
had of that brightness.

00:15:57.523 --> 00:16:03.563 align:middle line:84%
Did you experience a-- it was a
little girl that came in and--

00:16:03.563 --> 00:16:04.497 align:middle line:90%
>> EA: Well.

00:16:04.497 --> 00:16:05.665 align:middle line:84%
>> LG: -- her face
appeared, right?

00:16:05.665 --> 00:16:07.834 align:middle line:84%
>> EA: Yeah, on this
butterfly wing when I went

00:16:07.834 --> 00:16:12.872 align:middle line:84%
up into this beautiful valley
ultra real and the colors

00:16:12.872 --> 00:16:15.141 align:middle line:84%
of the butterfly, and gain
this is not a butterfly

00:16:15.141 --> 00:16:17.677 align:middle line:84%
like some entomologist on
earth could give you genus

00:16:17.677 --> 00:16:18.778 align:middle line:90%
and species.

00:16:18.778 --> 00:16:21.748 align:middle line:84%
It's simply the best
word I have to convey

00:16:21.748 --> 00:16:24.918 align:middle line:84%
about what was my mode
of transportation.

00:16:24.918 --> 00:16:26.286 align:middle line:90%
>> LG: OK.

00:16:26.286 --> 00:16:29.289 align:middle line:84%
>> EA: We move up into that
valley and there were millions

00:16:29.289 --> 00:16:31.691 align:middle line:84%
of other butterflies
and they were flying

00:16:31.691 --> 00:16:35.829 align:middle line:84%
in this tremendous lovely
river of life and color

00:16:35.829 --> 00:16:38.832 align:middle line:84%
and we would sweep down
into that lush greenery.

00:16:38.832 --> 00:16:42.769 align:middle line:84%
And as we flew by, buds
on trees and blossoms

00:16:42.769 --> 00:16:44.370 align:middle line:90%
on flowers would open up.

00:16:44.370 --> 00:16:45.772 align:middle line:90%
>> LG: Wow.

00:16:45.772 --> 00:16:48.675 align:middle line:84%
>> EA: And these rich textures
and colors beyond the rainbow,

00:16:48.675 --> 00:16:51.044 align:middle line:84%
waterfalls and the
sparkling pools--

00:16:51.044 --> 00:16:52.312 align:middle line:90%
>> LG: Wow.

00:16:52.312 --> 00:16:54.948 align:middle line:84%
>> EA: -- below us, souls
are dancing a lots of joy

00:16:54.948 --> 00:16:57.450 align:middle line:84%
and mirth children
playing, dogs are jumping,

00:16:57.450 --> 00:17:02.155 align:middle line:90%
incredible-- just idyllic scene.

00:17:02.155 --> 00:17:03.656 align:middle line:84%
>> LG: Is this what
you would describe

00:17:03.656 --> 00:17:06.525 align:middle line:84%
as your best definition
of heaven?

00:17:06.525 --> 00:17:08.394 align:middle line:84%
>> EA: Well, it's
only a part of it

00:17:08.394 --> 00:17:11.764 align:middle line:84%
because in fact there
were two main realms

00:17:11.764 --> 00:17:15.335 align:middle line:84%
that I visited beyond
that earthworm eye view.

00:17:15.335 --> 00:17:17.803 align:middle line:84%
This first one, this
gateway realm,

00:17:17.803 --> 00:17:22.142 align:middle line:84%
that beautiful idyllic valley
with the souls dancing,

00:17:22.142 --> 00:17:25.812 align:middle line:90%
souls between lives and that

00:17:25.812 --> 00:17:30.984 align:middle line:84%
on that butterfly
wing, a beautiful girl.

00:17:30.984 --> 00:17:33.953 align:middle line:84%
Absolutely gorgeous and
she never said a word

00:17:33.953 --> 00:17:36.389 align:middle line:84%
and I can remember her face,
I can remember her clothing,

00:17:36.389 --> 00:17:39.325 align:middle line:84%
every thing, how she was sitting
with her knees together off

00:17:39.325 --> 00:17:42.862 align:middle line:84%
to the side and looking at
me with this lovely smile.

00:17:42.862 --> 00:17:44.931 align:middle line:90%
This look of pure love.

00:17:44.931 --> 00:17:46.399 align:middle line:90%
>> LG: Was she younger?

00:17:46.399 --> 00:17:48.067 align:middle line:90%
Was she older?

00:17:48.067 --> 00:17:51.271 align:middle line:84%
>> EA: She looked to
be kind of, I mean,

00:17:51.271 --> 00:17:52.906 align:middle line:90%
it's so hard to put in age.

00:17:52.906 --> 00:17:54.040 align:middle line:90%
>> LG: In age, yes.

00:17:54.040 --> 00:17:55.942 align:middle line:84%
>> EA: But I would say
kind of a perfect age.

00:17:55.942 --> 00:17:58.578 align:middle line:84%
You know, she was in
her early or mid 20s.

00:17:58.578 --> 00:18:03.249 align:middle line:84%
Beautiful girl with sparkling
blue eyes, high forehead,

00:18:03.249 --> 00:18:07.687 align:middle line:84%
you know, high cheek
bones, and this lovely smile

00:18:07.687 --> 00:18:09.422 align:middle line:84%
and the message coming
in from her.

00:18:09.422 --> 00:18:12.759 align:middle line:84%
And again this is pure concept,
not words, but the words

00:18:12.759 --> 00:18:15.962 align:middle line:84%
that I wrote down later
and she never said a word.

00:18:15.962 --> 00:18:17.664 align:middle line:90%
This was just her thoughts

00:18:17.664 --> 00:18:20.166 align:middle line:84%
and the word coming
straight into my awareness.

00:18:20.166 --> 00:18:26.472 align:middle line:84%
You are loved and cherished
dearly forever, you have nothing

00:18:26.472 --> 00:18:30.944 align:middle line:84%
to fear, there's nothing you
can do wrong in this realm,

00:18:30.944 --> 00:18:33.146 align:middle line:90%
in that spiritual realm.

00:18:33.146 --> 00:18:34.380 align:middle line:90%
You will be taken care off.

00:18:34.380 --> 00:18:35.648 align:middle line:90%
>> LG: Wow.

00:18:35.648 --> 00:18:41.588 align:middle line:84%
>> EA: And it was such a
beautiful unconditionally loving

00:18:41.588 --> 00:18:43.189 align:middle line:90%
and comforting beyond words.

00:18:43.189 --> 00:18:45.692 align:middle line:84%
I mean, just to even recall
it now just gives me shivers

00:18:45.692 --> 00:18:50.029 align:middle line:84%
because it was so perfect
and wonderful and welcoming.

00:18:50.029 --> 00:18:54.367 align:middle line:84%
Nothing to fear, there's such
a deep lesson in that for all

00:18:54.367 --> 00:18:58.271 align:middle line:84%
of us because in fact that old
saying there's nothing to fear

00:18:58.271 --> 00:19:01.975 align:middle line:84%
but fear itself is far truer
than I ever, ever knew before.

00:19:01.975 --> 00:19:03.309 align:middle line:90%
>> LG: Right.

00:19:03.309 --> 00:19:04.877 align:middle line:84%
>> EA: And that fears the
source of any of the darkness

00:19:04.877 --> 00:19:08.081 align:middle line:84%
and the badness and the material
realm as well as in some

00:19:08.081 --> 00:19:10.450 align:middle line:84%
of the lower aspects
of the spiritual realm.

00:19:10.450 --> 00:19:12.385 align:middle line:84%
>> LG: As you know
about the brain,

00:19:12.385 --> 00:19:17.257 align:middle line:84%
when you recall this experience,
it lights up certain centers

00:19:17.257 --> 00:19:18.391 align:middle line:90%
of your brain that enables you

00:19:18.391 --> 00:19:21.694 align:middle line:84%
to re-live the experience
in certain ways.

00:19:21.694 --> 00:19:23.863 align:middle line:90%
Is that what you're feeling?

00:19:23.863 --> 00:19:26.899 align:middle line:84%
>> EA: Well, it's-- that's
very much the case, I would--

00:19:26.899 --> 00:19:30.036 align:middle line:84%
it's important to
understand that a big part

00:19:30.036 --> 00:19:33.506 align:middle line:84%
of the lesson I learned from
this journey as a neuroscientist

00:19:33.506 --> 00:19:36.209 align:middle line:84%
as one whose interested
in brain, in mind

00:19:36.209 --> 00:19:40.179 align:middle line:84%
and consciousness is it
showed me very clearly

00:19:40.179 --> 00:19:43.449 align:middle line:84%
that there is a tremendous
aspect

00:19:43.449 --> 00:19:48.655 align:middle line:84%
of our conscious awareness
moment to moment that even

00:19:48.655 --> 00:19:52.258 align:middle line:84%
if we had perfect infinite
knowledge of the state

00:19:52.258 --> 00:19:53.960 align:middle line:90%
of the physical brain, moment

00:19:53.960 --> 00:19:56.763 align:middle line:84%
to moment we would be
missing a tremendous amount

00:19:56.763 --> 00:19:59.499 align:middle line:90%
of how to explain it all.

00:19:59.499 --> 00:20:02.735 align:middle line:84%
And that is the crucial
element that it showed me

00:20:02.735 --> 00:20:04.003 align:middle line:90%
and no uncertain terms,

00:20:04.003 --> 00:20:06.939 align:middle line:84%
a consciousness is
the thing that exist.

00:20:06.939 --> 00:20:11.244 align:middle line:84%
That consciousness is
actually enriched tremendously

00:20:11.244 --> 00:20:16.149 align:middle line:84%
when it's freed up from the
shackles of the physical brain

00:20:16.149 --> 00:20:19.385 align:middle line:84%
and the human mind dumb down
on this side of the veil

00:20:19.385 --> 00:20:20.787 align:middle line:84%
and that's a very
important thing.

00:20:20.787 --> 00:20:22.188 align:middle line:84%
>> LG: Yeah, where
does conscious--

00:20:22.188 --> 00:20:23.923 align:middle line:84%
where does consciousness exist
in the brain that hasn't been--

00:20:23.923 --> 00:20:27.593 align:middle line:84%
>> EA: It-- consciousness
it not created by the brain.

00:20:27.593 --> 00:20:28.528 align:middle line:90%
>> LG: Oh--

00:20:28.528 --> 00:20:29.395 align:middle line:84%
>> EA: That is the
important thing.

00:20:29.395 --> 00:20:31.130 align:middle line:90%
This is an old idea--

00:20:31.130 --> 00:20:34.000 align:middle line:84%
>> LG: None of the lobes, none
of the cortexes, its not--

00:20:34.000 --> 00:20:35.335 align:middle line:90%
>> EA: No, I mean

00:20:35.335 --> 00:20:37.971 align:middle line:84%
in neuroscience we know a
tiny bit about consciousness.

00:20:37.971 --> 00:20:41.007 align:middle line:84%
We know that there seems
to be an ignition system

00:20:41.007 --> 00:20:43.643 align:middle line:84%
in what's called a
reticular activating formation

00:20:43.643 --> 00:20:48.314 align:middle line:84%
down the lower brain stem
that that seems to be firing

00:20:48.314 --> 00:20:51.317 align:middle line:90%
in about a 40 hertz signal rate

00:20:51.317 --> 00:20:54.420 align:middle line:84%
up into what we call
thalamocortical loops did going

00:20:54.420 --> 00:20:55.755 align:middle line:90%
up in the thalamus which is part

