And I can not tell you
what a shock that was.

00:39:29.868 --> 00:39:32.370 align:middle line:90%
Never in my life had I expected

00:39:32.370 --> 00:39:34.439 align:middle line:84%
that they ended up
getting married.

00:39:34.439 --> 00:39:36.341 align:middle line:84%
>> LG: So, your mind
started racing I'm sure.

00:39:36.341 --> 00:39:37.442 align:middle line:90%
>> EA: My mind was racing

00:39:37.442 --> 00:39:40.212 align:middle line:84%
in fact I decided
I'd better pull over.

00:39:40.212 --> 00:39:43.281 align:middle line:84%
And she said, "They
had three children."

00:39:43.281 --> 00:39:44.583 align:middle line:90%
>> LG: Oh my goodness.

00:39:44.583 --> 00:39:47.786 align:middle line:84%
>> EA: But your youngest
sister died two years ago.

00:39:47.786 --> 00:39:50.288 align:middle line:90%
That would have been in 1998.

00:39:50.288 --> 00:39:53.992 align:middle line:84%
And they're still grieving over
that so it's not a good time

00:39:53.992 --> 00:39:56.061 align:middle line:90%
to come back in their lives.

00:39:56.061 --> 00:39:59.998 align:middle line:84%
And that phone call that--
then I hang up and that was it.

00:39:59.998 --> 00:40:02.767 align:middle line:90%
That's what I was left with.

00:40:02.767 --> 00:40:04.069 align:middle line:84%
>> LG: Turns you
entirely on upside down.

00:40:04.069 --> 00:40:05.604 align:middle line:84%
>> EA: It turned
everything upside down

00:40:05.604 --> 00:40:08.440 align:middle line:90%
and I really didn't realize.

00:40:08.440 --> 00:40:11.309 align:middle line:84%
You know, at that time I
just kind of stuffed it.

00:40:11.309 --> 00:40:15.947 align:middle line:84%
But I came to realize
over months and years then

00:40:15.947 --> 00:40:20.685 align:middle line:84%
in fact it started my
whole life unraveling.

00:40:20.685 --> 00:40:21.820 align:middle line:90%
>> LG: How--

00:40:21.820 --> 00:40:23.655 align:middle line:84%
>> EA: It started
everything to turn around

00:40:23.655 --> 00:40:30.195 align:middle line:84%
and it was seven years later
that finally my sisters walking

00:40:30.195 --> 00:40:32.764 align:middle line:84%
on the beach one day on a
family vacations said, "Well,

00:40:32.764 --> 00:40:35.066 align:middle line:84%
don't you think it's
about time you reached

00:40:35.066 --> 00:40:37.569 align:middle line:90%
out to your birth family again."

00:40:37.569 --> 00:40:38.670 align:middle line:90%
And I thought, oh gosh.

00:40:38.670 --> 00:40:41.239 align:middle line:84%
I remembered how
that it took me over.

00:40:41.239 --> 00:40:42.908 align:middle line:84%
But I thought I guess
they're right.

00:40:42.908 --> 00:40:46.711 align:middle line:84%
So, I wrote another letter that
was in a year before my coma.

00:40:46.711 --> 00:40:49.414 align:middle line:90%
That was in August of 2007.

00:40:49.414 --> 00:40:53.251 align:middle line:84%
Wrote a letter to them and ended
up getting a positive response

00:40:53.251 --> 00:40:57.289 align:middle line:84%
and October 5th, 2007,
I met my birth parents.

00:40:57.289 --> 00:40:59.925 align:middle line:90%
I had not seen them in 54 years.

00:40:59.925 --> 00:41:03.295 align:middle line:84%
And that is a beautiful
story in its own right.

00:41:03.295 --> 00:41:04.095 align:middle line:90%
>> LG: Wow.

00:41:04.095 --> 00:41:05.230 align:middle line:90%
>> EA: An amazing adventure.

00:41:05.230 --> 00:41:08.266 align:middle line:84%
Meeting them, the next
day meeting my brother

00:41:08.266 --> 00:41:09.734 align:middle line:90%
and sister and of course--

00:41:09.734 --> 00:41:11.102 align:middle line:90%
>> LG: Oh my goodness.

00:41:11.102 --> 00:41:13.138 align:middle line:84%
>> EA: -- introducing adoptive
and birth families and a lot

00:41:13.138 --> 00:41:17.175 align:middle line:84%
of back and forth,
tremendous beautiful experience

00:41:17.175 --> 00:41:20.779 align:middle line:84%
that has been, always
a little bitter sweet.

00:41:20.779 --> 00:41:22.347 align:middle line:90%
Because at the back of it all,

00:41:22.347 --> 00:41:26.518 align:middle line:84%
deep at the core was Betsy
[assumed spelling] was gone long

00:41:26.518 --> 00:41:28.053 align:middle line:90%
before I even knew she existed.

00:41:28.053 --> 00:41:31.556 align:middle line:84%
And that part always
brought some sadness.

00:41:31.556 --> 00:41:35.660 align:middle line:84%
There wasn't a lot
that I knew about her,

00:41:35.660 --> 00:41:40.832 align:middle line:84%
wasn't like they really like
dwelling on that topic and--

00:41:40.832 --> 00:41:42.634 align:middle line:84%
>> LG: How old was
she when she passed?

00:41:42.634 --> 00:41:45.670 align:middle line:84%
>> EA: She was 36
when she passed.

00:41:45.670 --> 00:41:49.107 align:middle line:84%
And in fact, that's where
everything comes together

00:41:49.107 --> 00:41:50.909 align:middle line:90%
to answer your question.

00:41:50.909 --> 00:41:53.445 align:middle line:84%
Because my other sister
Cathy [assumed spelling],

00:41:53.445 --> 00:41:55.146 align:middle line:90%
by birth sister, had told me

00:41:55.146 --> 00:41:57.916 align:middle line:84%
that someday she would
send me a picture of Betsy.

00:41:57.916 --> 00:42:01.353 align:middle line:84%
And that picture arrived about
four months after my coma

00:42:01.353 --> 00:42:04.222 align:middle line:84%
when I was deeply
into wrestling,

00:42:04.222 --> 00:42:05.790 align:middle line:90%
we're trying to understand it.

00:42:05.790 --> 00:42:09.594 align:middle line:84%
I'd come to realize that it
was a very authentic journey

00:42:09.594 --> 00:42:13.498 align:middle line:84%
that absolutely validated so
many other experiences reported

00:42:13.498 --> 00:42:16.334 align:middle line:84%
over 3,000 years, not just
near death experiences

00:42:16.334 --> 00:42:19.170 align:middle line:84%
but afterlife literature
back to the ancient Greeks--

00:42:19.170 --> 00:42:19.871 align:middle line:90%
>> LG: Wow.

00:42:19.871 --> 00:42:20.905 align:middle line:90%
>> EA: -- and Egyptians.

00:42:20.905 --> 00:42:23.808 align:middle line:84%
And the stories of
mystics and prophets

00:42:23.808 --> 00:42:25.677 align:middle line:90%
over thousands of years.

00:42:25.677 --> 00:42:28.346 align:middle line:84%
All validated very
real and understanding

00:42:28.346 --> 00:42:32.717 align:middle line:84%
about consciousness and yet
to me as I read more and more

00:42:32.717 --> 00:42:34.653 align:middle line:84%
of these near-death
experiences coming

00:42:34.653 --> 00:42:37.255 align:middle line:90%
to realize where was my father.

00:42:37.255 --> 00:42:40.325 align:middle line:84%
If I had scripted this
my father who had passed

00:42:40.325 --> 00:42:43.428 align:middle line:84%
over four years before my coma
would have been there front

00:42:43.428 --> 00:42:44.229 align:middle line:90%
and center.

00:42:44.229 --> 00:42:46.231 align:middle line:90%
He was no where to be found.

00:42:46.231 --> 00:42:48.767 align:middle line:84%
And who in the world
was that beautiful girl

00:42:48.767 --> 00:42:49.801 align:middle line:90%
in the butterfly wings?

00:42:49.801 --> 00:42:51.169 align:middle line:90%
>> LG: Right, right.

00:42:51.169 --> 00:42:53.071 align:middle line:84%
>> EA: I saw her many times,
every time I pass through there

00:42:53.071 --> 00:42:55.407 align:middle line:84%
and I remember her
face so perfectly.

00:42:55.407 --> 00:42:58.109 align:middle line:84%
I will never forget
everything about her.

00:42:58.109 --> 00:43:00.045 align:middle line:90%
I remember her so clearly.

00:43:00.045 --> 00:43:02.814 align:middle line:84%
I knew I'd never
met her in my life.

00:43:02.814 --> 00:43:05.150 align:middle line:84%
And that part was
a huge mystery.

00:43:05.150 --> 00:43:09.487 align:middle line:84%
And it all came together four
months after my coma and I got

00:43:09.487 --> 00:43:13.391 align:middle line:84%
that picture from Cathy
with this poem emblazed

00:43:13.391 --> 00:43:17.362 align:middle line:84%
into [inaudible] that's in the
book When I'm not here Tomorrow,

00:43:17.362 --> 00:43:21.199 align:middle line:84%
a beautiful poem that was
written by David Romano.

00:43:21.199 --> 00:43:25.637 align:middle line:84%
And that, I remember tears just
filling my eyes as I was looking

00:43:25.637 --> 00:43:27.172 align:middle line:84%
at this picture,
reading this poem,

00:43:27.172 --> 00:43:29.207 align:middle line:84%
it was just such an
emotional moment.

00:43:29.207 --> 00:43:32.410 align:middle line:84%
I put that up on my dresser
and it was the next morning

00:43:32.410 --> 00:43:35.013 align:middle line:84%
when I was reading an Elizabeth
Kubler Ross' book on Death

00:43:35.013 --> 00:43:37.782 align:middle line:84%
and Dying, a story
about a 13-year-old girl

00:43:37.782 --> 00:43:40.552 align:middle line:84%
who had a powerful
near death experience.

00:43:40.552 --> 00:43:41.953 align:middle line:90%
>> LG: Wow.

00:43:41.953 --> 00:43:45.423 align:middle line:84%
>> EA: Deep coma was welcome to
heaven by her brother was shown

00:43:45.423 --> 00:43:48.860 align:middle line:84%
that incredible unconditional
love and its infinite power.

00:43:48.860 --> 00:43:52.397 align:middle line:84%
He helped her to make a
decision about coming back

00:43:52.397 --> 00:43:54.099 align:middle line:90%
to this world which he did.

00:43:54.099 --> 00:43:57.936 align:middle line:84%
And when she did, she was
mystified over the experience.

00:43:57.936 --> 00:44:00.972 align:middle line:84%
She would talk with her
father, I don't understand,

00:44:00.972 --> 00:44:02.841 align:middle line:90%
I don't have a brother.

00:44:02.841 --> 00:44:07.212 align:middle line:84%
And he said, "Well, you did
but he died four months,

00:44:07.212 --> 00:44:08.613 align:middle line:84%
three months before
you were born

00:44:08.613 --> 00:44:11.149 align:middle line:90%
so we never told you about it."

00:44:11.149 --> 00:44:13.952 align:middle line:84%
And I looked up at the
picture on by dresser.

00:44:13.952 --> 00:44:17.522 align:middle line:84%
And immediately saw that
girl on the butterfly wing.

00:44:17.522 --> 00:44:20.225 align:middle line:84%
And in the picture,
she's looking at me like,

00:44:20.225 --> 00:44:22.327 align:middle line:90%
do you finally get it?

00:44:22.327 --> 00:44:24.262 align:middle line:90%
And it was the most shocking--

00:44:24.262 --> 00:44:25.530 align:middle line:90%
>> LG: Wow.

00:44:25.530 --> 00:44:27.265 align:middle line:84%
>> EA: -- revelation of my
entire existence reaching

00:44:27.265 --> 00:44:29.901 align:middle line:84%
across all those
dimensions proving--

00:44:29.901 --> 00:44:31.302 align:middle line:90%
>> LG: Yes.

00:44:31.302 --> 00:44:34.339 align:middle line:84%
>> EA: -- with great power to
me the reality of that journey

00:44:34.339 --> 00:44:37.942 align:middle line:84%
in a way that I would
never ever doubt it again.

00:44:37.942 --> 00:44:40.111 align:middle line:84%
>> LG: So, you had never
seen her picture before

00:44:40.111 --> 00:44:43.414 align:middle line:84%
and this beautiful picture
of a face that came to you

00:44:43.414 --> 00:44:46.851 align:middle line:84%
in that experience-- in the
near-death experience showed

00:44:46.851 --> 00:44:49.621 align:middle line:84%
up in a photo of your sister
who passed three years of prior.

00:44:49.621 --> 00:44:50.922 align:middle line:90%
>> EA: Yes.

00:44:50.922 --> 00:44:53.992 align:middle line:84%
And it was-- I think a big
catalyst and it was reading

00:44:53.992 --> 00:44:57.328 align:middle line:84%
that Elizabeth Kubler
Ross story because--

00:44:57.328 --> 00:44:58.229 align:middle line:90%
>> LG: Which part of it?

00:44:58.229 --> 00:44:59.597 align:middle line:90%
The acceptance?

00:44:59.597 --> 00:45:02.267 align:middle line:84%
>> EA: Well, the fact that this
girl I had always, you know,

00:45:02.267 --> 00:45:05.436 align:middle line:84%
to that point I'd come
to think that, you know,

00:45:05.436 --> 00:45:09.941 align:middle line:84%
such a guardian angel as I'd
come to call her in my writings

00:45:09.941 --> 00:45:13.778 align:middle line:84%
with somebody of great
importance to you in this life.

00:45:13.778 --> 00:45:16.581 align:middle line:84%
And so, I kept looking
for people, you know,

00:45:16.581 --> 00:45:20.318 align:middle line:84%
in my life who I'd met
in this physical life.

00:45:20.318 --> 00:45:24.656 align:middle line:84%
And it never entered my mind
that it could be a soul,

00:45:24.656 --> 00:45:28.493 align:middle line:84%
a very dear close
importance to me

00:45:28.493 --> 00:45:30.962 align:middle line:84%
that I'd never known
in this life.

00:45:30.962 --> 00:45:33.231 align:middle line:84%
And that was the
revelation that I really got

00:45:33.231 --> 00:45:35.834 align:middle line:84%
from that Elizabeth
Kubler Ross story.

00:45:35.834 --> 00:45:39.270 align:middle line:84%
>> LG: Did you ever think
about the words that--

00:45:39.270 --> 00:45:43.608 align:middle line:84%
the message, I should say, that
she gave you that you are loved,

00:45:43.608 --> 00:45:47.512 align:middle line:90%
that you are-- that you are OK.

00:45:47.512 --> 00:45:51.583 align:middle line:84%
Has that changed the way
that you live your life now?

00:45:51.583 --> 00:45:53.952 align:middle line:84%
>> EA: It's totally
changed everything.

00:45:53.952 --> 00:45:57.255 align:middle line:84%
Part of it is realizing, as
I pointed out in the book.

00:45:57.255 --> 00:46:03.294 align:middle line:84%
I kind of used the metaphor,
the whole story of my adoption

00:46:03.294 --> 00:46:06.464 align:middle line:84%
and the fact that I was kind of
separated from my roots and in

00:46:06.464 --> 00:46:12.070 align:middle line:84%
that sense was kind of
unloving, unlovable detached

00:46:12.070 --> 00:46:14.072 align:middle line:90%
from my true identity.

00:46:14.072 --> 00:46:14.873 align:middle line:90%
And--

00:46:14.873 --> 00:46:16.074 align:middle line:90%
>> LG: So, on a soul level,

00:46:16.074 --> 00:46:17.375 align:middle line:84%
that's what you were
really, really looking for.

00:46:17.375 --> 00:46:18.643 align:middle line:84%
>> EA: That's-- well, that's
kind of what I was seeing

00:46:18.643 --> 00:46:22.213 align:middle line:84%
in my life because of that
adoption story in my life.

00:46:22.213 --> 00:46:25.350 align:middle line:84%
And yet what I came to see in
my coma journey very clearly.

00:46:25.350 --> 00:46:29.754 align:middle line:84%
And this is the truth that
applies to all of us is

00:46:29.754 --> 00:46:34.959 align:middle line:84%
that when we buy into this
kind of scientific materialism

00:46:34.959 --> 00:46:37.695 align:middle line:90%
in this secular thinking,

00:46:37.695 --> 00:46:41.733 align:middle line:84%
the material world
is all that there is.

00:46:41.733 --> 00:46:47.071 align:middle line:84%
That's false and its terrible
misleading because it allows us

00:46:47.071 --> 00:46:53.378 align:middle line:84%
to forget that we are divine,
that we are infinitely loved--

00:46:53.378 --> 00:46:54.712 align:middle line:90%
>> LG: Right, right.

00:46:54.712 --> 00:46:56.915 align:middle line:84%
>> EA: -- by the creative
power of this entire universe.

00:46:56.915 --> 00:46:58.283 align:middle line:90%
>> LG: Yes.

00:46:58.283 --> 00:47:01.953 align:middle line:84%
>> EA: And are forever loved
and it's an unconditional love

00:47:01.953 --> 00:47:05.123 align:middle line:90%
that demands nothing from us.

00:47:05.123 --> 00:47:09.494 align:middle line:84%
Now of course, I know also the
richer aspects of our journey,

00:47:09.494 --> 00:47:13.164 align:middle line:84%
of our many lives, incarnation
that it's all about love,

00:47:13.164 --> 00:47:15.600 align:middle line:84%
compassion, forgiveness
in the ascendance

00:47:15.600 --> 00:47:17.402 align:middle line:84%
of our souls in that
higher realm.

00:47:17.402 --> 00:47:18.703 align:middle line:90%
So, it's not as if we come in

00:47:18.703 --> 00:47:22.106 align:middle line:84%
and can just do anything
we want and be mean and--

00:47:22.106 --> 00:47:23.408 align:middle line:90%
>> LG: Right.

00:47:23.408 --> 00:47:24.809 align:middle line:84%
>> EA: -- you'll pass out
pain and suffering to others

00:47:24.809 --> 00:47:28.980 align:middle line:84%
because we are here to learn the
lessons that that is not the way

00:47:28.980 --> 00:47:31.649 align:middle line:90%
to live and we will reap.

00:47:31.649 --> 00:47:34.018 align:middle line:84%
You know, what we saw when
it comes to that kind of--

00:47:34.018 --> 00:47:35.553 align:middle line:84%
>> LG: So, you know
this for sure now?

00:47:35.553 --> 00:47:36.087 align:middle line:90%
>> EA: Yes.

00:47:36.087 --> 00:47:37.288 align:middle line:90%
>> LG: Yes.

00:47:37.288 --> 00:47:38.656 align:middle line:84%
>> EA: I mean that is
part of the deepest lesson

00:47:38.656 --> 00:47:42.894 align:middle line:84%
that was there in that
core realm is that love,

00:47:42.894 --> 00:47:45.663 align:middle line:84%
that unconditional love,
compassion, forgiveness,

00:47:45.663 --> 00:47:49.834 align:middle line:84%
coming to see soul mates in the
very richest that soul mate--

00:47:49.834 --> 00:47:51.569 align:middle line:84%
a soul mate might
be someone who,

00:47:51.569 --> 00:47:53.338 align:middle line:84%
before my coma, I
saw as my enemy.

00:47:53.338 --> 00:47:56.607 align:middle line:84%
Soul mates come in many
forms, we're here to learn

00:47:56.607 --> 00:47:59.944 align:middle line:84%
from our soul mates and
to teach our soul mates.

00:47:59.944 --> 00:48:00.912 align:middle line:90%
And after my coma--

00:48:00.912 --> 00:48:02.347 align:middle line:90%
>> LG: Interesting.

00:48:02.347 --> 00:48:05.116 align:middle line:84%
>> EA: I came to see that often,
a soul mate might be someone

00:48:05.116 --> 00:48:08.186 align:middle line:84%
who before I'd seen as
an enemy or my nemesis

00:48:08.186 --> 00:48:10.922 align:middle line:84%
who in fact was there to
help me learn a very deep

00:48:10.922 --> 00:48:11.656 align:middle line:90%
though lessons.

00:48:11.656 --> 00:48:12.490 align:middle line:90%
>> LG: Wow.

00:48:12.490 --> 00:48:13.825 align:middle line:90%
>> EA: And the other way around.

00:48:13.825 --> 00:48:18.096 align:middle line:84%
Often I'm helping them learn
a very deep and tough lesson

00:48:18.096 --> 00:48:19.731 align:middle line:84%
and that is what
we are here to do.

00:48:19.731 --> 00:48:24.035 align:middle line:84%
This is soul school, this is
where we learn these lessons

00:48:24.035 --> 00:48:28.873 align:middle line:84%
but to begin to comprehend them,
you must have an open concept

00:48:28.873 --> 00:48:32.510 align:middle line:84%
about reincarnation and about
how it's not just birth to death

00:48:32.510 --> 00:48:35.246 align:middle line:84%
because if you just think it's
birth to death nothing more,

00:48:35.246 --> 00:48:38.282 align:middle line:84%
there's no way you can possibly
see the much grander scheme

00:48:38.282 --> 00:48:39.617 align:middle line:90%
of it all.

00:48:39.617 --> 00:48:40.918 align:middle line:84%
>> LG: Well, speaking of grand
schemes, you ever thought

00:48:40.918 --> 00:48:44.455 align:middle line:90%
about why you came back.

00:48:44.455 --> 00:48:48.693 align:middle line:84%
>> EA: Well, for the longest
time I was trying to explain it,

00:48:48.693 --> 00:48:50.395 align:middle line:84%
you know, as a brain
based phenomenon,

00:48:50.395 --> 00:48:52.930 align:middle line:84%
as a neuroscientist
trying to learn something

00:48:52.930 --> 00:48:56.234 align:middle line:84%
about consciousness then I have
the revelation that showed me

00:48:56.234 --> 00:49:00.471 align:middle line:84%
that it actually was
so much that validation

00:49:00.471 --> 00:49:04.675 align:middle line:84%
of spiritual journeys of sharing
similarities with thousands

00:49:04.675 --> 00:49:07.645 align:middle line:84%
of other journeys reported
over thousands of years.

00:49:07.645 --> 00:49:09.047 align:middle line:90%
>> LG: Yeah.

00:49:09.047 --> 00:49:11.883 align:middle line:84%
>> EA: And as I would talk more
and more with other experiences

00:49:11.883 --> 00:49:14.085 align:middle line:84%
and with other people
about all this.

00:49:14.085 --> 00:49:15.119 align:middle line:90%
People would keep telling me,

00:49:15.119 --> 00:49:17.121 align:middle line:84%
you know this happened
for a reason.

00:49:17.121 --> 00:49:18.322 align:middle line:90%
>> LG: Yes, yes.

00:49:18.322 --> 00:49:20.324 align:middle line:84%
>> EA: And of course I
was trying to approach it

00:49:20.324 --> 00:49:22.860 align:middle line:84%
as the objective
doctor, you know,

00:49:22.860 --> 00:49:25.663 align:middle line:84%
as much as I could realizing
that they're deep lessons there

00:49:25.663 --> 00:49:28.533 align:middle line:90%
for all of us but denying

00:49:28.533 --> 00:49:31.135 align:middle line:84%
that there could be
anything special about me.

00:49:31.135 --> 00:49:36.874 align:middle line:84%
And in fact I still think that
the special thing about me is

00:49:36.874 --> 00:49:39.544 align:middle line:84%
that I'm just like
everybody else.

00:49:39.544 --> 00:49:43.414 align:middle line:84%
I have the same, you know,
problems and foibles in life.

00:49:43.414 --> 00:49:48.786 align:middle line:84%
I'm absolutely no saint
at all and, you know,

00:49:48.786 --> 00:49:50.588 align:middle line:84%
I'm just like all
the rest of us.

00:49:50.588 --> 00:49:56.494 align:middle line:84%
I'm just, you know, a normal
person and so many times

00:49:56.494 --> 00:49:59.263 align:middle line:84%
when people would say that
to me about this happened

00:49:59.263 --> 00:50:00.965 align:middle line:90%
to you for a special reason.

00:50:00.965 --> 00:50:04.836 align:middle line:84%
I would think back to the fact
I was given away as a baby,

00:50:04.836 --> 00:50:08.372 align:middle line:84%
and that gives me
a real commonality

00:50:08.372 --> 00:50:10.808 align:middle line:90%
with each and every one of us.

00:50:10.808 --> 00:50:15.313 align:middle line:84%
Because we all have that kind
of sense of being detached.

00:50:15.313 --> 00:50:17.815 align:middle line:84%
>> LG: Have you even tapped
into that message though

00:50:17.815 --> 00:50:21.652 align:middle line:84%
to tell people who have been
adopted that they are loved?

00:50:21.652 --> 00:50:23.354 align:middle line:84%
>> EA: Oh, I tap into
that message a lot.

00:50:23.354 --> 00:50:23.888 align:middle line:90%
And this--

00:50:23.888 --> 00:50:25.289 align:middle line:90%
>> LG: Good.

00:50:25.289 --> 00:50:26.491 align:middle line:84%
>> EA: -- and the thing is of
course this message is not just

00:50:26.491 --> 00:50:29.026 align:middle line:84%
for adpotees to realize
that they are deeply loved

00:50:29.026 --> 00:50:32.363 align:middle line:84%
and cherished and have
been in this earthly realm

00:50:32.363 --> 00:50:36.367 align:middle line:84%
by that family that had to
let them go out of the love.

00:50:36.367 --> 00:50:38.736 align:middle line:84%
But it's also that
much grander message,

00:50:38.736 --> 00:50:41.305 align:middle line:84%
the same message
though, to all the rest

00:50:41.305 --> 00:50:43.407 align:middle line:90%
of us, to every one of us.

00:50:43.407 --> 00:50:44.275 align:middle line:90%
>> LG: That we are loved.

00:50:44.275 --> 00:50:45.409 align:middle line:90%
>> EA: That each and every one

00:50:45.409 --> 00:50:48.613 align:middle line:84%
of us is an infinitely
powerful light being,

00:50:48.613 --> 00:50:53.618 align:middle line:84%
a spiritual being eternal loved
beyond our wildest imagination

00:50:53.618 --> 00:50:55.786 align:middle line:90%
by the creator of this universe.

00:50:55.786 --> 00:50:57.788 align:middle line:90%
And that we are all one.

00:50:57.788 --> 00:50:58.856 align:middle line:90%
>> LG: Yes.

00:50:58.856 --> 00:50:59.957 align:middle line:84%
>> EA: And it's a
beautiful gift to share.

00:50:59.957 --> 00:51:01.759 align:middle line:84%
>> LG: That was the
biggest message I got

00:51:01.759 --> 00:51:04.529 align:middle line:84%
when I had my experience
was that of oneness.

00:51:04.529 --> 00:51:07.965 align:middle line:84%
Now, you spend a lot of time in
meditation now still don't you?

00:51:07.965 --> 00:51:10.067 align:middle line:84%
>> EA: Well, I came
to realize of course

00:51:10.067 --> 00:51:12.537 align:middle line:84%
that consciousness
was right at the core

00:51:12.537 --> 00:51:14.772 align:middle line:84%
of everything I was
trying to understand.

00:51:14.772 --> 00:51:17.742 align:middle line:84%
And also to realize that
the linguistic brain,

00:51:17.742 --> 00:51:21.479 align:middle line:84%
that little voice in our head
actually gets in the way.

00:51:21.479 --> 00:51:25.183 align:middle line:84%
You know, before my coma, I
felt the voice in our head is,

00:51:25.183 --> 00:51:28.152 align:middle line:84%
you know, that's the pinnacle
of intellectual achievement

00:51:28.152 --> 00:51:29.420 align:middle line:90%
in the known universe.

00:51:29.420 --> 00:51:33.558 align:middle line:84%
Is that little rational
logical kind of scientific voice

00:51:33.558 --> 00:51:35.626 align:middle line:84%
of our thinking mind
of the intellect

00:51:35.626 --> 00:51:39.230 align:middle line:90%
of the well read inteligencia.

00:51:39.230 --> 00:51:42.667 align:middle line:84%
Well, fact of the matter is
there's far deeper knowing

00:51:42.667 --> 00:51:44.735 align:middle line:90%
that's far richer than anything

00:51:44.735 --> 00:51:47.672 align:middle line:84%
that voice can ever
put into words.

00:51:47.672 --> 00:51:49.240 align:middle line:90%
I knew as a neurosurgeon

00:51:49.240 --> 00:51:52.710 align:middle line:84%
that that little voice is
just the tiniest fraction

00:51:52.710 --> 00:51:55.346 align:middle line:84%
of your brain is involved
in that little voice.

00:51:55.346 --> 00:51:58.683 align:middle line:84%
And there're are two regions
that have to do with production

00:51:58.683 --> 00:52:00.251 align:middle line:90%
of speech and reception

00:52:00.251 --> 00:52:02.887 align:middle line:84%
and understanding
of speech connected.

00:52:02.887 --> 00:52:04.555 align:middle line:84%
But they're very small
part of the brain.

00:52:04.555 --> 00:52:06.691 align:middle line:84%
That's one of those
things that kind of leads

00:52:06.691 --> 00:52:09.560 align:middle line:84%
to a misunderstanding about
what is consciousness.

00:52:09.560 --> 00:52:10.995 align:middle line:84%
>> LG: What is chatter
for that reason?

00:52:10.995 --> 00:52:12.063 align:middle line:84%
>> EA: Yeah, what
is mind chatter?

00:52:12.063 --> 00:52:13.564 align:middle line:84%
We know what is a
mind chatter is.

00:52:13.564 --> 00:52:16.934 align:middle line:84%
And of course I also knew of the
experiments from Benjamin Libet

00:52:16.934 --> 00:52:19.403 align:middle line:84%
and others beginning
in early 1980s

00:52:19.403 --> 00:52:22.340 align:middle line:84%
that that little voice is
not even the decision maker.

00:52:22.340 --> 00:52:26.510 align:middle line:84%
That little voice is actually
informed of the decision of 100

00:52:26.510 --> 00:52:30.448 align:middle line:84%
to 150 milliseconds after
the decision is made.

00:52:30.448 --> 00:52:31.749 align:middle line:90%
Yeah.

00:52:31.749 --> 00:52:32.450 align:middle line:84%
>> LG: So, your mind chatter
is not the decision maker?

00:52:32.450 --> 00:52:33.718 align:middle line:90%
>> EA: No, not at all.

00:52:33.718 --> 00:52:35.453 align:middle line:84%
And you-- that's
something that--

00:52:35.453 --> 00:52:36.787 align:middle line:90%
>> LG: How do you know that?

00:52:36.787 --> 00:52:39.423 align:middle line:84%
>> EA: Neuroscientist have
known that for 30 or 40 years.

00:52:39.423 --> 00:52:42.226 align:middle line:84%
That the little voice
is-- and it--

00:52:42.226 --> 00:52:45.863 align:middle line:84%
I reference this in my book, the
experiments of Benjamin Libet

00:52:45.863 --> 00:52:48.099 align:middle line:84%
and then others who
followed suit.

00:52:48.099 --> 00:52:50.902 align:middle line:84%
And I described the
experiment on my book.

00:52:50.902 --> 00:52:54.005 align:middle line:90%
But basically that little voice,

00:52:54.005 --> 00:52:58.109 align:middle line:84%
you can show an electrical
recording of cortical activity

00:52:58.109 --> 00:53:03.281 align:middle line:84%
of the brain that when we make a
spontaneous freewill decisions,

00:53:03.281 --> 00:53:06.651 align:middle line:84%
the decision is actually
made before

00:53:06.651 --> 00:53:10.221 align:middle line:84%
that voice says it's
made the decision.

00:53:10.221 --> 00:53:14.292 align:middle line:84%
And that was well documented
and has been well shown.

00:53:14.292 --> 00:53:17.962 align:middle line:84%
Of course then, in the
traditional psychology world,

00:53:17.962 --> 00:53:21.599 align:middle line:84%
that starts bringing up issues
of consciousness, subconscious,

00:53:21.599 --> 00:53:24.168 align:middle line:84%
unconscious, superconscious,
you know,

00:53:24.168 --> 00:53:26.437 align:middle line:84%
universal consciousness
et cetera.

00:53:26.437 --> 00:53:29.573 align:middle line:84%
And again, those were all
linguistic definitions

00:53:29.573 --> 00:53:33.044 align:middle line:84%
and they're kind of
misleading like so many aspects

00:53:33.044 --> 00:53:35.446 align:middle line:90%
of the linguistic brain are.

00:53:35.446 --> 00:53:38.983 align:middle line:84%
The linguistic brain is
heavily tied to self and ego.

00:53:38.983 --> 00:53:42.820 align:middle line:84%
Self and ego are important
ideas in kind of survival

00:53:42.820 --> 00:53:46.857 align:middle line:84%
and materialist Darwinian
world but they get in the way

00:53:46.857 --> 00:53:50.127 align:middle line:84%
of a deeper knowing that
is our true consciousness.

00:53:50.127 --> 00:53:53.998 align:middle line:84%
I came to realize meditation
is the key to getting there.

00:53:53.998 --> 00:53:54.532 align:middle line:90%
Getting deep--

00:53:54.532 --> 00:53:55.599 align:middle line:90%
>> LG: Yes.

00:53:55.599 --> 00:53:56.434 align:middle line:84%
>> EA: -- exploring
into consciousness--

00:53:56.434 --> 00:53:57.268 align:middle line:90%
>> LG: Yes.

00:53:57.268 --> 00:53:58.502 align:middle line:90%
>> EA: -- is absolutely the key.

00:53:58.502 --> 00:54:00.771 align:middle line:84%
>> LG: Did you meditate
before your experience as--

00:54:00.771 --> 00:54:03.708 align:middle line:84%
>> EA: I had done something
called silver mind control back

00:54:03.708 --> 00:54:04.642 align:middle line:90%
when I was in college.

00:54:04.642 --> 00:54:05.910 align:middle line:90%
>> LG: Right.

00:54:05.910 --> 00:54:07.812 align:middle line:84%
>> EA: The parachute team,
we did silver mind control

00:54:07.812 --> 00:54:09.847 align:middle line:90%
to practice free fall formations

00:54:09.847 --> 00:54:12.350 align:middle line:84%
and meditation before
we went and did the job.

00:54:12.350 --> 00:54:14.051 align:middle line:84%
So, it helped us to
do a better job--

00:54:14.051 --> 00:54:14.752 align:middle line:90%
>> LG: Great.

00:54:14.752 --> 00:54:16.153 align:middle line:90%
>> EA: -- in freefall.

00:54:16.153 --> 00:54:19.223 align:middle line:84%
But then I let the meditation
go and it was only after my coma

00:54:19.223 --> 00:54:21.125 align:middle line:90%
that I got back into it.

00:54:21.125 --> 00:54:23.160 align:middle line:84%
And currently I'm
very interested

00:54:23.160 --> 00:54:25.162 align:middle line:90%
in using sound techniques.

00:54:25.162 --> 00:54:26.364 align:middle line:90%
>> LG: Yes.

00:54:26.364 --> 00:54:28.332 align:middle line:84%
>> EA: I mentioned in my
book Robert Monroe's work

00:54:28.332 --> 00:54:33.270 align:middle line:84%
Out of Body Experiences that
he had using what he call the

00:54:33.270 --> 00:54:36.340 align:middle line:84%
